Japanese: ジャンジャック＿操縦基本

/pさん、
人形使いならわかるはず。
English: /p, as a Puppeteer yourself, you should understand.

Japanese:
今日は、あなたにとって
記念すべき日だ。
English: Today is going to be a memorable day for you.

Japanese:
ついに、世界の頂点に
挑戦することができたんだ。
English: Finally, you'll realise what it means to face the supreme.

Japanese:
/pさんはこれまで、
たくさんの人形使いと戦い、
勝利してきた。
English: Until now, you've fought many Puppeteers and won.

Japanese:
たとえ、姉と出会うという幸運
があったとはいえ、この栄誉は
あなた自身で掴み取ったものだ。
English: For example, you've had the fortune of meeting my sister, which is an honour you seized all by yourself.

Japanese:
たとえボクに敗れるとしても、
頂点と戦ったという栄誉は残る。
English: And, even if you lose to me, you'll still have the honour of knowing you fought against the supreme.

Japanese:
あなたの戦いは、
無駄ではなかった。
English: Your efforts in this battle won't be in vain.

Japanese: ジャンジャック＿操縦嬉しい

English: Now then, let's begin.

Japanese:
今、あなたの目の前にいるのは、
世界最高の人形使い。
English: At this very moment, you're about to face the best Puppeteer in the entire world.

Japanese:
数百年の歴史が生んだ
無敵の人形使い
/c5ジャン・ジャック・ダンクール/c3。
English: An unrivalled Puppeteer born from hundreds of years of cultivation, /c5Jean-Jacques Dancourt/c3.

Japanese:
その身をもって体験するといい。
ダンクールの人形剣技を。
English: You can experience it first-hand. The swordsmanship of a Dancourt mech.
The Galouye Workshop...
It's you, from the other day!!
Jacques!!!
Hey, sister.
Sister!?

Japanese: アンマリー＿ちょっとした驚き

English: Jacques...
What are you doing here?

Japanese:
姉さんが、こんなところで
修行してるなんてね。
驚いたよ。
English: To think my older sister is training in such a place. I'm surprised.

Japanese: アンマリー＿ちょっとした驚き

English: ...Ah... That...

Japanese:
姉さんより強い人形使いが
いるらしいね。
English: I heard that there was someone even stronger than you here.
...Yeah...

Japanese: ジャンジャック＿悲しい
それはマズイんじゃない？
English: That's no good, is it?

Japanese:
姉さんもダンクールなんだから。
家名を汚すようなマネは
しないで欲しいな。
English: You're a Dancourt too. I wish you wouldn't tarnish our family name.
You're a burden.

Japanese:
それでもダンクールの
一族なのかい？
English: And, despite that we're still supposed to call you a member of the Dancourt family?

Japanese:
こいつ、
なんだか頭に来るやつだな。
English: This kid is ticking me off for some reason.

Japanese:
アンマリーも
ちゃんと言い返せよ！
English: Anne-Marie, how are you going to retort?!

Japanese: ジャンジャック＿悲しい

English: Anyway, sister.

Japanese:
ダンクールの名に
傷をつけるようなことだけは
しないで欲しいんだ。
English: I just don't want you to do anything that would disgrace the Dancourt name.

Japanese:
姉の不始末は、
弟のボクが責任をとるよ。
English: My sisters shortcomings are my responsibility, as her younger brother.

Japanese:
/pさん、
ボクと勝負しよう。
English: /p, have a match against me.

Japanese:
本当のダンクールの力を
見せるよ。
English: I'll show you the might of a real Dancourt.
What?!

Japanese:
なんで/pがお前と
戦わなきゃなんないんだ？
English: Why should /p have to fight you?

Japanese:
ダンクール家は、
数百年続く人形使いの家系。
English: The Dancourt family's Pupeteering lineage stretches back hundreds of years.

Japanese:
姉さんが、
ずいぶん不甲斐ない所を
みせてるみたいだからね。
English: It seems that my sister has been putting on a rather pathetic display of that legacy.

Japanese:
本当のところを証明しないと
いけないんだ。
English: But I'll prove the truth.

Japanese:
/pさんじゃ、
ダンクールに遠く及ばない
ってことをね。
English: I'll show /p just how much he's lacking compared to a Dancourt.

Japanese:
もう、こいつ、
本当に頭に来るぜ！
English: Sheesh, this kid is really getting on my nerves!

Japanese:
本当は、こんなやつに
付き合う必要はないんだが……
English: In truth, it's not like we owe him any obligation to go along with this...

Japanese:
頭にくるから
やってやれ、/p！
English: But I can't take any more of this. Get him, /p!
...Stop it...
Anne-Marie?
...Just stop...
It's impossible...

Japanese: 弟のジャックは、天才よ。
English: My younger brother is a genius.

Japanese:
何百年もの伝統が生んだ
史上最高の人形使い。
English: Our family has kept this tradition for hundreds of years, and he's the best Puppeteer ever known.

Japanese:
怪我するのがオチ。
無駄なことはやめて……。
English: Nothing will come out of this except you getting hurt. Stop wasting your energy on futile things...

Japanese: ケイ＿むしゃくしゃするＬ
お前、バカじゃねぇのか！
English: Are you stupid or something!?

Japanese:
お前……ずっと、
そんなこと考えてたのか！！
English: You... Have you always thought of it that way!!?
You really are an idiot.
I knew that anyway...

Japanese: ケイ＿むしゃくしゃするＬ

English: Darn it!
/p, get him good!
Yeah.

Japanese: 話はまとまったようだね。
English: Looks like you've finished your discussion.
What say we get started?
